// =============================================================================
// Samavāya BI — Dataset Service
// =============================================================================
// The dataset service is the semantic layer of the BI platform. It abstracts
// raw database tables / views / queries into a business-friendly model of
// dimensions, measures, relationships, and calculated fields that the query
// and report services consume.
//
// Power BI equivalent: Semantic Model + DAX measures + relationships.
// Looker equivalent:   LookML model + dimensions/measures/joins.
//
// Design notes
// ------------
//   * Every entity is tenant/company/branch scoped through the standard
//     TenantContext header — no vertical-specific shortcuts.
//   * Formulas (calculated fields) are stored as raw expressions here.
//     The formula parser + evaluator lives in the query service; the dataset
//     service only accepts or rejects syntactically-valid expressions.
//   * Permissions are expressed at the dataset level with optional row
//     filters. Column-level masking is a v2 concern, explicitly noted below.
//   * Relationships are one-directional declarations; the query engine
//     walks them to plan joins. Do not store pre-computed join SQL here.
//
// Related docs
// ------------
//   * docs/BI_CONSOLIDATION_ROADMAP.md — sprint plan
//   * docs/adr/0001-bi-platform-consolidation.md — why this exists
//   * docs/adr/0002-bi-proto-contracts.md — contracts & service relationships
// =============================================================================

